Of all the games that were on sale during Steam Summer Sale 2012, this is still the one game that I wanted the most. Even though it wasn't even featured on the front page during the sale, I think The Dream Machine deserves much attention. I've been wanting to play the full game since it first appeared here on Steam. Now I finally have it! (got a Steam key straight from the developer themself!) I hope that someday it will be featured in the next Humble Indie Bundle for the world to see.

This one is for the imaginitive minds who are looking for adventure in obscure miniature worlds. It's a point-n-click gem with claymation visual style which you very rarely see in video games. If you're a fan of Telltale Games' episodic point-and-click adventures like Monkey Island, Wallace & Gromit, Machinarium, or other claymation style games like The Neverhood, Skullmonkeys, definitely grab this. What you will encounter is a dream game waiting to be unraveled.

// Roth Sothy

